    Z "Mh..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1779
translate spanish d19d_4facd82b:

    # Ne "Hey, sleepyhead!"
    Ne "¡Ey, dormilón!"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1782
translate spanish d19d_e1bf71ea:

    # "You slowly regain consciousness. It's quite bright already. Did you oversleep?"
    "Recuperas la consciencia poco a poco. Ya está bastante claro. ¿Te habrás quedado dormido de más?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1785
translate spanish d19d_667d36ac:

    # Z "...what time is it?"
    Z "... ¿qué hora es?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1788
translate spanish d19d_81399316:

    # Ne "Pretty late, actually. But your [persistent.da] suggested to let you rest for a little longer. You can blame her for that."
    Ne "Bastante tarde, la verdad. Pero tu [persistent.da] sugirió dejarte descansar un poco más. Puedes culparla a ella por eso."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1791
translate spanish d19d_997faf15:

    # S "We are ready to go when you are. I took the time to go over our information about the three places again, and Neith prepared some breakfast."
    S "Estamos listos para irnos cuando tú quieras. Aproveché para repasar la información sobre los tres lugares, y Neith preparó algo de desayuno."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1794
translate spanish d19d_6a17293f:

    # Ne "It's... just an appreciation for last night, okay. Don't read too much into it."
    Ne "Es... solo un detalle por lo de anoche, ¿vale? No le des más vueltas."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1797
translate spanish d19d_9df2910a:

    # Z "Well I do appreciate it nonetheless. This caring side of you, you could show it more often."
    Z "Pues yo lo aprecio de todos modos. Ese lado tuyo tan atento podrías mostrarlo más seguido."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1800
translate spanish d19d_614a2a3c_2:

    # Ne "..."
    Ne "..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1803
translate spanish d19d_e52e2f90:

    # Z "Take a seat. I want to take a look at these again..."
    Z "Siéntate. Quiero revisar esto otra vez..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1804
translate spanish d19d_b8b71a28:

    # S "Do you want me to give you a short summary to refresh your memories?"
    S "¿Quieres que te haga un pequeño resumen para refrescarte la memoria?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1805
translate spanish d19d_78e5d4b5:

    # Z "Go ahead."
    Z "Adelante."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1806
translate spanish d19d_930811bc:

    # S "So, first, there's the bazaar, with the local trader. He, or anyone in there, might know more about the ancient ruins we're looking for."
    S "Primero, está el bazar, con el comerciante local. Él, o cualquiera ahí dentro, podría saber más sobre las ruinas antiguas que buscamos."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1807
translate spanish d19d_e67a132b:

    # S "And as we discussed yesterday, Neith should stay away from this one. Too many chances for her identity to be revealed."
    S "Y como discutimos ayer, Neith debería mantenerse lejos de ese. Demasiadas posibilidades de que su identidad se descubra."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1808
translate spanish d19d_038eef4c:

    # S "So either you or me should go investigate. Whichever you prefer."
    S "Así que o tú o yo deberíamos investigar. Como prefieras."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1811
translate spanish d19d_41d4aefd:

    # Z "We will have to decide. Now: the elderly man."
    Z "Habrá que decidir. Ahora: el anciano."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1812
translate spanish d19d_bee3e3ab:

    # S "Yes, something of a local wise man. Supposedly, people, even caravans go out of their ways to seek his counsel. If anyone has access to older documentation or word of mouth knowledge, it's going to be him."
    S "Sí, algo así como un sabio local. Supuestamente, la gente, incluso las caravanas, se desvían para pedirle consejo. Si alguien tiene acceso a documentos antiguos o conocimientos transmitidos, será él."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1815
translate spanish d19d_f5c93a2a:

    # Z "And finally the ruins."
    Z "Y por último, las ruinas."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1816
translate spanish d19d_266710eb:

    # Ne "Those seem to be rather ancient. They have a similar layout as most of the public buildings of the smaller settlements."
    Ne "Parecen bastante antiguas. Tienen un diseño similar al de la mayoría de edificios públicos de los asentamientos pequeños."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1817
translate spanish d19d_0b91bbed:

    # Ne "It's hard to say though, if it's just a more recent dilapidated structure or whether it is one of the original ancient constructions."
    Ne "Aunque es difícil decir si se trata solo de una estructura más reciente en ruinas o si realmente es una de las construcciones originales."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1818
translate spanish d19d_fd9f6101:

    # Ne "Perhaps... there is still something to be found."
    Ne "Quizá... aún haya algo por encontrar."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1819
translate spanish d19d_693d3f00:

    # S "These are our options. So, what do we want to investigate first?"
    S "Estas son nuestras opciones. Entonces, ¿qué queremos investigar primero?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1895
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_0ec6793e:

    # "Coming back from the ruins, [S] and Neith are carefully inspecting the scroll, while you take the opportunity to resupply, before sitting back down with them to prepare your next outing..."
    "Al volver de las ruinas, [S] y Neith inspeccionan cuidadosamente el pergamino, mientras aprovechas para reabastecerte, antes de sentarte de nuevo con ellas para preparar la siguiente salida..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1898
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_2d6b690b:

    # Z "So, what did you find out?"
    Z "Entonces, ¿qué averiguaste?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1901
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_f0cd0173:

    # S "I think it's a page from someone's journal. It lists a few transactions, some comments on the quality of the goods that were traded."
    S "Creo que es una página del diario de alguien. Anota algunas transacciones y comentarios sobre la calidad de los bienes que se comerciaban."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1902
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_83fa2005:

    # Z "Anything of particular interest?"
    Z "¿Algo de especial interés?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1903
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_d9bf3f9b:

    # S "Not really. The only thing that stands out to me is that there are talks about trading honey, and it seems like it's locally sourced."
    S "No mucho. Lo único que me llama la atención es que hablan de comerciar miel, y parece que era de producción local."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1904
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_600dd56d:

    # Ne "Not even I have had freshly made honey in a long while."
    Ne "Ni yo he probado miel fresca en mucho tiempo."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1905
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_874242df:

    # Ne "As far as I know, we haven't had much in the way of flowers and bees for at least fifty or more years."
    Ne "Que yo sepa, no hemos tenido muchas flores ni abejas en al menos cincuenta años o más."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1906
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_b80843ff:

    # S "Well, now we know that this page is genuinely old."
    S "Bueno, ahora sabemos que esta página es realmente antigua."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1909
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_d79424f5:

    # S "...anyway, that's all we know. I suggest we move on? It could be just an irrelevant document after all."
    S "...en fin, eso es todo lo que sabemos. ¿Seguimos adelante? Después de todo podría ser solo un documento irrelevante."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1912
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_3127e5da:

    # Z "Let's see what's up next."
    Z "Veamos qué sigue."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1918
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_19eb0da0:

    # "As you sit, concentrating on cleaning and sharpening your blade, you are called to attention by your [persistent.da], who is quickly sharing her findings."
    "Mientras te concentras en limpiar y afilar tu espada, tu [persistent.da] llama tu atención y comparte rápidamente lo que ha encontrado."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1920
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_0130df3f:

    # "You take a look at the map, and you realise quickly that this map is centered on an entirely different area and is totally useless to your current task."
    "Echas un vistazo al mapa y te das cuenta enseguida de que está centrado en una zona completamente distinta y es totalmente inútil para la tarea actual."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1923
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_664d64c3:

    # Z "I'm sorry to say this, but this map... Well, it's not showing anything around here."
    Z "Lamento decirlo, pero este mapa... bueno, no muestra nada de esta zona."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1926
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_98f885ba:

    # S "Well, and there I thought..."
    S "Bueno, y yo que pensaba..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1929
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_bcd5d63e:

    # Z "It shows a body of water nearby, and I'm pretty sure there hasn't been one for ages anywhere around here."
    Z "Muestra un cuerpo de agua cercano, y estoy bastante seguro de que no ha habido ninguno por aquí en siglos."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1933
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_b88b63dc:

    # S "...and that's it."
    S "... y eso es todo."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1936
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_2c8d5bfa:

    # Z "Women never have it easy, out in the desert. Did you at least manage to stay out of trouble?"
    Z "Las mujeres nunca lo tienen fácil en el desierto. ¿Al menos lograste mantenerte fuera de problemas?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1940
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_9364046e:

    # S "I did, yes. They kept it civil, all things considered."
    S "Sí, lo hice. Se mantuvieron cordiales, considerando todo."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1943
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_26f0725f:

    # Z "Alright. I suggest we take a look at the other places as well, though. Having a map is good, but I want to see if we can identify some of the landmarks."
    Z "De acuerdo. Aun así sugiero que veamos los otros lugares también. Tener un mapa está bien, pero quiero comprobar si podemos identificar algunos puntos de referencia."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1946
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_01441d70:

    # Ne "Sounds good. Where to next, then?"
    Ne "Suena bien. ¿Adónde vamos ahora?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1953
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_bc33e510:

    # S "That... depends. Let's just say nothing serious happened. It was part of Mandisa's training to be prepared for moments like these."
    S "Eso... depende. Digamos que no pasó nada serio. Fue parte del entrenamiento de Mandisa estar preparada para momentos así."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1956
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_f2d414b3:

    # S "In the end, I played him like a fiddle, got his map, and left. But as we just learned..."
    S "Al final lo manejé como quise, conseguí su mapa y me fui. Pero como acabamos de aprender..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1959
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_06006295:

    # Z "I suggest we take a look at the other places as well, then. There is still a chance."
    Z "Sugiero que echemos un vistazo a los otros lugares también. Todavía hay una oportunidad."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1962
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_a177763c:

    # Ne "Sounds good. What's next on the list, then?"
    Ne "Suena bien. ¿Qué sigue en la lista entonces?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1968
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_6187c97b:

    # S "...and, for better or worse, I got what I wanted. But as we just learned..."
    S "... y, para bien o para mal, conseguí lo que quería. Pero como acabamos de aprender..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1971
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_6fbfcd33:

    # Z "The desert is an unforgiving place, and many more men and women will want to put their hands on you. That's why it's important to always strive to stay in control of the situation."
    Z "El desierto no perdona, y muchos más hombres y mujeres querrán echarte mano. Por eso es importante esforzarse siempre en mantener el control de la situación."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1974
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_ca585b32:

    # S "You're right, [persistent.dad]. I should be more prepared."
    S "Tienes razón, [persistent.dad]. Debería estar más preparada."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1979
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_fc6e4f66:

    # S "...and unfortunately, I didn't get what I wanted. I should have been more prepared in dealing with that bastard."
    S "... y por desgracia, no conseguí lo que quería. Debería haber estado mejor preparada para tratar con ese bastardo."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1982
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_722d1f6c:

    # Z "Don't be discouraged about what happened, try to learn from it. The desert is an unforgiving place, and the men and women out use whatever advantage they have."
    Z "No te desanimes por lo que pasó, intenta aprender de ello. El desierto no perdona, y la gente usa cualquier ventaja que tenga."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1983
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_369c8830:

    # Z "Today's humiliation might sting, but it will serve as a lesson. The next time, you will come out on top. Such is the law of the desert."
    Z "La humillación de hoy puede doler, pero servirá de lección. La próxima vez saldrás victoriosa. Así es la ley del desierto."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1986
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_061251f0:

    # S "Today... was certainly a reminder. But you are right. I will learn from it."
    S "Hoy... fue sin duda un recordatorio. Pero tienes razón. Aprenderé de ello."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1989
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_2703ca53:

    # Z "Good. Then let us see where to go next."
    Z "Bien. Entonces veamos adónde ir después."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1995
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_460687c2:

    # "As you return to the tent, you find [S] practicing with the crossbow, as [Ne] observes her carefully."
    "Al regresar a la tienda, encuentras a [S] practicando con la ballesta, mientras [Ne] la observa atentamente."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1996
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_46d79424:

    # "When they notice you, curiosity flickers across their faces. They turn towards you, ready to hear about your findings."
    "Cuando te ven, la curiosidad se refleja en sus rostros. Se giran hacia ti, listas para escuchar lo que descubriste."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:1999
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_f651c87d:

    # Z "...and that's all there was. The chief wasn't willing to talk to me."
    Z "...y eso fue todo. El jefe no quiso hablar conmigo."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2000
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_4c9dfaa7:

    # Z "We need to look somewhere else. Are you guys ready for another attempt?"
    Z "Necesitamos buscar en otro lugar. ¿Están listas para otro intento?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2003
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_62d79c4d:

    # S "Bring it on, [persistent.dad]. Where to next?"
    S "Venga, [persistent.dad]. ¿A dónde vamos ahora?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2010
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_039e30a3:

    # "As you return to the tent, you find [S] practicing with the crossbow, as [Ne] observes her carefully. When they notice you, curiosity flickers across their faces. They turn towards you, ready to hear about your findings."
    "Al regresar a la tienda, encuentras a [S] practicando con la ballesta, mientras [Ne] la observa atentamente. Cuando te ven, la curiosidad se refleja en sus rostros. Se giran hacia ti, listas para escuchar lo que descubriste."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2013
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_6bc8079e:

    # Z "...and then he showed me a points to use as reference. This might be what we were looking for."
    Z "...y entonces me mostró unos puntos de referencia. Puede que esto sea lo que buscábamos."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2016
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_4ae684c7:

    # S "Well done! That sounded quite easy. Sometimes the rumors are indeed true."
    S "¡Bien hecho! Eso sonó bastante fácil. A veces los rumores resultan ser ciertos."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2019
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_c768667c:

    # Z "Well done, your majesty."
    Z "Bien hecho, su majestad."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2022
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_5e1db005:

    # Ne "Oh, ehm... you're welcome!"
    Ne "Oh, ehm... ¡de nada!"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2028
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_e8aca73e:

    # Z "That's for a good start, but we still have the time to make sure the information is correct."
    Z "Es un buen comienzo, pero aún tenemos tiempo para asegurarnos de que la información sea correcta."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2029
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_0ad79cc5:

    # Z "It's best we look for another place. Perhaps someone out there knows more."
    Z "Será mejor que busquemos en otro lugar. Quizá alguien allá fuera sepa más."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2032
translate spanish d19d_first_visit_aftermath_62d79c4d_1:

    # S "Bring it on, [persistent.dad]. Where to next?"
    S "Vamos allá, [persistent.dad]. ¿Adónde vamos ahora?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2046
translate spanish d19d_second_visit_aftermath_02b7fca5:

    # "The weather changes fast as [S] returns to the camp: A holy storm looms, not far away."
    "El clima cambia rápido cuando [S] regresa al campamento: una tormenta sagrada se avecina, no muy lejos."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2048
translate spanish d19d_second_visit_aftermath_6c5534e3:

    # "The weather changes fast as you return to the camp: A holy storm looms, not far away."
    "El clima cambia rápido cuando regresas al campamento: una tormenta sagrada se avecina, no muy lejos."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2049
translate spanish d19d_second_visit_aftermath_ebba065e:

    # "If the storm turns your way, you realise that you will have to change your plans accordingly. Things could get hairy."
    "Si la tormenta se dirige hacia vosotros, te das cuenta de que tendrás que ajustar tus planes en consecuencia. Las cosas podrían ponerse feas."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2052
translate spanish d19d_second_visit_aftermath_3270504d:

    # Ne "[S]... how does it look? Are we safe?"
    Ne "[S]... ¿cómo se ve? ¿Estamos a salvo?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2055
translate spanish d19d_second_visit_aftermath_7229c7cd:

    # S "For now, yes. The wind is getting stronger... If it turns, we will have to face the storm."
    S "Por ahora sí. El viento está aumentando... Si cambia, tendremos que enfrentarnos a la tormenta."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2058
translate spanish d19d_second_visit_aftermath_7570dfa0:

    # Z "Perhaps we don't have to sit around, after all. Join us, [S]."
    Z "Quizá no tengamos que quedarnos de brazos cruzados, después de todo. Únete a nosotros, [S]."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2062
translate spanish d19d_second_visit_aftermath_0553fbfd:

    # "You sit together..."
    "Os sentáis juntos..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2065
translate spanish d19d_second_visit_aftermath_1167b75f:

    # Z "Look, girls... we can discuss what happened out there later."
    Z "Mirad, chicas... podemos hablar más tarde de lo que ha pasado ahí fuera."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2067
translate spanish d19d_second_visit_aftermath_f94394f9:

    # Z "The good thing is that the old man gave us locations we can work with."
    Z "Lo bueno es que el anciano nos dio ubicaciones con las que podemos trabajar."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2068
translate spanish d19d_second_visit_aftermath_613c9fb6:

    # Z "And since this storm is most likely going to stay with us for a little while, we have to decide whether we want to take a look at one of these places again, or hunker down for the night."
    Z "Y dado que esta tormenta probablemente se quede con nosotros un rato, debemos decidir si queremos revisar uno de estos lugares otra vez o refugiarnos por la noche."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2071
translate spanish d19d_second_visit_aftermath_df4d2948:

    # Ne "I have been outside during storms, but never somewhere as exposed as this... do we really need to brave the storm like that?"
    Ne "He estado afuera durante tormentas, pero nunca en un lugar tan expuesto como este... ¿de verdad tenemos que enfrentarnos a la tormenta así?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2075
translate spanish d19d_second_visit_aftermath_f341c4d3:

    # S "I don't think you should, in any case. We have already visited the ruins. The rest is up to either [persistent.dad] or me."
    S "No creo que tú debas, en cualquier caso. Ya visitamos las ruinas. El resto depende de [persistent.dad] o de mí."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2077
translate spanish d19d_second_visit_aftermath_3af5a1b5:

    # S "That depends... we could still visit the ruins. Don't worry, we will be fine."
    S "Depende... todavía podríamos visitar las ruinas. No te preocupes, estaremos bien."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2080
translate spanish d19d_second_visit_aftermath_536566b1:

    # Z "Unfortunately, we have not yet found any clue about the whereabouts of this temple."
    Z "Por desgracia, aún no hemos encontrado ninguna pista sobre el paradero de este templo."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2081
translate spanish d19d_second_visit_aftermath_1cda8268:

    # Z "The storm is most likely going to stay with us for a little while. I suggest we move quickly and try to stay ahead of the storm."
    Z "La tormenta probablemente se quede con nosotros un rato. Sugiero que nos movamos rápido e intentemos mantenernos por delante de ella."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2084
translate spanish d19d_second_visit_aftermath_35a4e328:

    # Q "I have been outside during storms, but out here... I guess there is no choice?"
    Q "He estado afuera durante tormentas, pero aquí fuera... supongo que no hay otra opción, ¿no?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2087
translate spanish d19d_second_visit_aftermath_16c1fb2d:

    # S "I don't think so. But it's fine, the storm is not going to be a problem."
    S "No lo creo. Pero está bien, la tormenta no será un problema."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2090
translate spanish d19d_second_visit_aftermath_db1e3c74:

    # S "Let's get out there, one last time?"
    S "¿Salimos una última vez?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2093
translate spanish d19d_second_visit_aftermath_caa5c624:

    # Z "Let's make it quick."
    Z "Hagámoslo rápido."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2101
translate spanish d19d_ruins_chosen_3f9742b5:

    # Z "I think we should do this one together, what do you two say?"
    Z "Creo que deberíamos hacer esto juntos, ¿qué decís vosotras?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2104
translate spanish d19d_ruins_chosen_edbc0921:

    # S "The ruins, huh? I'm not sure they haven't been cleaned out already, but..."
    S "¿Las ruinas, eh? No estoy segura de que no hayan sido saqueadas ya, pero..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2107
translate spanish d19d_ruins_chosen_782d00ab:

    # Ne "I'm in!"
    Ne "¡Yo me apunto!"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2113
translate spanish d19d_ruins_chosen_d0c37e8b:

    # Ne "In case... you wanted my opinion."
    Ne "Por si acaso... querías mi opinión."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2116
translate spanish d19d_ruins_chosen_f623e65b:

    # Z "You're part of this too, yes."
    Z "Tú también formas parte de esto, sí."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2119
translate spanish d19d_ruins_chosen_c19ac202:

    # "She smiles..."
    "Sonríe..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2120
translate spanish d19d_ruins_chosen_b1ba906a:

    # S "Fine by me. Let's make our way to those ruins."
    S "Por mí está bien. Vamos hacia esas ruinas."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2123
translate spanish d19d_ruins_chosen_9e93702f:

    # "You pack some essential supplies and leave the tent, heading deeper into the desert in search of the Elder's temple..."
    "Empacas algunos suministros esenciales y sales de la tienda, adentrándote más en el desierto en busca del templo del Anciano..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2128
translate spanish d19d_ruins_chosen_2cec12de:

    # Z "The ruins are our next destination. Pack your essentials, girls. Let's try our luck there."
    Z "Las ruinas son nuestro próximo destino. Empaquen lo esencial, chicas. Probemos suerte allí."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2129
translate spanish d19d_ruins_chosen_ef93ca4e:

    # Z "Remember, should something happen to separate us, this is where we will meet again."
    Z "Recordad, si algo llegara a separarnos, aquí es donde nos reuniremos otra vez."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2137
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_139530f5:

    # Z "I'm going to find out if the traders have any useful knowledge."
    Z "Voy a averiguar si los comerciantes tienen algún conocimiento útil."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2140
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_e3db018b:

    # S "Are you sure you don't want me along?"
    S "¿Seguro que no quieres que vaya contigo?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2143
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_caaff632:

    # Z "I am. You guys make yourselves comfortable, perhaps plan the route for the next ones."
    Z "Estoy segura. Vosotras poneos cómodas, quizá planeen la ruta para las siguientes."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2146
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_3e3237f2:

    # Ne "Comfortable sounds nice."
    Ne "Cómodo suena bien."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2149
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_9570544d:

    # S "It does indeed. Want to swap outfits and see who's wearing it better?"
    S "Sí que lo es. ¿Quieres intercambiar ropa y ver a quién le queda mejor?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2152
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_e4d84d98:

    # Ne "Would that even be a contest? I'm not just your Queen - I reign over dresses, too."
    Ne "¿Eso sería siquiera un concurso? No soy solo tu Reina: también domino sobre los vestidos."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2157
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_9a245252:

    # "Leaving the girls to their games, you make your way to the bazaar by foot, in search for the location of the Elder's temple..."
    "Dejando a las chicas con sus juegos, te diriges al bazar a pie, en busca de la ubicación del templo del Anciano..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2162
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_49765a6a:

    # Z "The old man already gave us a location, but I have not yet seen what the bazaar can offer. Perhaps there's still someone out there who knows more than he does."
    Z "El anciano ya nos dio una ubicación, pero aún no he visto qué puede ofrecernos el bazar. Quizá todavía haya alguien que sepa más que él."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2164
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_a5e8fa0b:

    # Z "I'm heading out to that bazaar. We must make sure whether the traders know something more than we already do."
    Z "Voy a dirigirme a ese bazar. Debemos asegurarnos de si los comerciantes saben algo más de lo que ya sabemos."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2167
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_22db3b44:

    # S "Stay safe out there, [persistent.dad]."
    S "Cuídate ahí fuera, [persistent.dad]."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2176
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_dc6fe3e1:

    # Z "The old man already gave us a location, but I will head out to the bazaar again. I will make him talk, if I have to."
    Z "El anciano ya nos dio una ubicación, pero volveré al bazar. Haré que hable, si es necesario."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2178
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_1bda35dd:

    # Z "I will try my luck out there at the bazaar again. If the chief doesn't want to help me out, then I have to find out what makes him wanting to."
    Z "Volveré a probar suerte en el bazar. Si el jefe no quiere ayudarme, tendré que averiguar qué lo hace cambiar de idea."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2185
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_aad55000:

    # Z "I've thought about it. [S], why don't you try your luck in that bazaar?"
    Z "Lo he pensado. [S], ¿por qué no pruebas suerte tú en ese bazar?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2188
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_81078ba6:

    # S "Can't be too hard. Check the place out, ask some locals for information, and come back."
    S "No puede ser tan difícil. Echar un vistazo, preguntar a algunos locales por información y volver."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2191
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_8bc22bde:

    # Ne "Eh... except for all the shady merchants and rough wastelanders."
    Ne "Eh... salvo por todos esos comerciantes turbios y maleantes del yermo."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2194
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_97518cff:

    # S "We deal with greedy merchants on a daily basis in your city, my Queen."
    S "Tratamos con comerciantes codiciosos a diario en tu ciudad, mi Reina."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2197
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_44e909e8:

    # Ne "I'm not sure it's the same as being in the city... but I am not the one sharing the streets with the rabble."
    Ne "No estoy segura de que sea lo mismo que estar en la ciudad... pero yo no soy la que comparte las calles con la chusma."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2198
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_f61b63e2:

    # Ne "Be careful regardless, okay?"
    Ne "De todas formas, ten cuidado, ¿vale?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2203
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_2fa0e955:

    # "After a few minutes of preparations, [S] makes her way to the settlement by foot, in search for the location of the Elder's temple."
    "Tras unos minutos de preparativos, [S] se dirige al asentamiento a pie, en busca de la ubicación del templo del Anciano."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2208
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_5a4c09c2:

    # Z "[S], are you willing to head to the bazaar under these circumstances?"
    Z "[S], ¿estás dispuesta a ir al bazar en estas circunstancias?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2211
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_52484a08:

    # Ne "I'm... not sure that's a good idea. With all those shady merchants...?"
    Ne "No estoy... segura de que sea buena idea. ¿Con todos esos comerciantes turbios...?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2214
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_f93bd2ec:

    # S "I don't mind. You and [persistent.dad] can prepare our things for our next trip tomorrow."
    S "No me importa. Tú y [persistent.dad] pueden preparar nuestras cosas para el próximo viaje mañana."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2219
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_f1477aab:

    # S "Check the place out, ask some locals for information, and come back."
    S "Echar un vistazo, preguntar a algunos locales por información y volver."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2220
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_35546595:

    # S "...besides the storm, that is."
    S "...bueno, aparte de la tormenta."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2223
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_cc6c279e:

    # Z "The storm should not become an issue. And if it does, don't hesitate to come back."
    Z "La tormenta no debería ser un problema. Y si lo es, no dudes en volver."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2224
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_684760c0:

    # Z "Be careful out there, [S]."
    Z "Ten cuidado ahí fuera, [S]."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2227
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_330fafd3:

    # S "I will be fine. I've been through one before, under much worse conditions."
    S "Estaré bien. Ya pasé por una antes, en condiciones mucho peores."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2233
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_f53d7724:

    # S "One last attempt, what do you say?"
    S "¿Un último intento, qué dices?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2236
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_8c2d0af1:

    # Z "Only if you want to. Else, I can go."
    Z "Solo si quieres. Si no, puedo ir yo."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2239
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_0e856992:

    # S "What are you saying? I've been through one before, under much worse conditions."
    S "¿Qué dices? Ya pasé por una antes, en condiciones mucho peores."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2240
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_8b7cbece:

    # S "I live for it as much as you do, [persistent.dad]."
    S "Lo disfruto tanto como tú, [persistent.dad]."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2249
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_89e94654:

    # Z "[S], do you want to give it another try? Even under these circumstances?"
    Z "[S], ¿quieres intentarlo otra vez? ¿Incluso en estas circunstancias?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2253
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_18713776:

    # S "...and settle the score with him? I can give it a try."
    S "... ¿y saldar cuentas con él? Puedo intentarlo."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2255
translate spanish d19d_bazaar_chosen_3ac6fb1c:

    # S "Maybe I was wrong to leave so soon, indeed. Let me see what I can do!"
    S "Quizá me equivoqué al irme tan pronto. ¡Déjame ver qué puedo hacer!"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2267
translate spanish d19d_old_man_chosen_ac532d52:

    # Z "I will take my chances with the old man. You two take it easy here until I am back."
    Z "Me arriesgaré con el anciano. Vosotras dos tomadlo con calma aquí hasta que regrese."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2270
translate spanish d19d_old_man_chosen_429de94d:

    # S "Look, he's ditching us at the first chance."
    S "Mira, nos abandona a la primera oportunidad."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2273
translate spanish d19d_old_man_chosen_820c163d:

    # Ne "Wow, look at you... and I thought I was the snarky one."
    Ne "Vaya, mírate... y yo pensaba que la sarcástica era yo."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2274
translate spanish d19d_old_man_chosen_a51b72e3:

    # Ne "Did you have any special motives to want to visit the old man? Maybe you have a thing for the elderly?"
    Ne "¿Tenías algún motivo especial para querer visitar al anciano? ¿Acaso te gustan los mayores?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2277
translate spanish d19d_old_man_chosen_36011753:

    # S "I won't even comment on that. Anyway, let's get you ready to go."
    S "Ni siquiera voy a comentar eso. En fin, vamos a prepararte para salir."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2283
translate spanish d19d_old_man_chosen_59f188ad:

    # "Moments later, [S] kisses your cheek and sees you off you into the desert, hoping you'll find clues to the Elder's temple."
    "Momentos después, [S] te besa en la mejilla y te despide mientras te adentras en el desierto, esperando que encuentres pistas sobre el templo del Anciano."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2288
translate spanish d19d_old_man_chosen_5c4d893b:

    # Z "The old man is last on the list. You girls stay safe here, I will seek him out and come back as soon as I can."
    Z "El anciano es el último de la lista. Vosotras quedaos seguras aquí, iré a buscarlo y volveré tan pronto como pueda."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2303
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_c2abcb30:

    # St "I'm here... it looks just like on the rough map."
    St "Ya estoy aquí... se ve justo como en el mapa rudimentario."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2306
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_917ce4f6:

    # St "It's quite tiny, compared to the endless markets in the city..."
    St "Es bastante pequeño, comparado con los interminables mercados de la ciudad..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2307
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_d9537cdf:

    # St "Now, where do I start? I need to find whoever is in charge of this place."
    St "Bien, ¿por dónde empiezo? Necesito encontrar a quien esté a cargo de este lugar."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2310
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_43ca57be:

    # S "Hm..."
    S "Hm..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2313
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_76226100:

    # St "She looks suspicious... and somehow familiar. Or maybe I'm imagining things."
    St "Ella se ve sospechosa... y de alguna forma familiar. O quizá me lo estoy imaginando."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2314
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_15f7f358:

    # St "Is she another Stalker? Perhaps a mercenary..."
    St "¿Será otra Acechadora? Tal vez una mercenaria..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2317
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_b4d763c3:

    # St "...I don't like the way she is looking at me. I better stay away from her."
    St "... No me gusta cómo me está mirando. Mejor me mantengo alejada."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2320
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_bccd7487:

    # St "These guys look like they could help... I wonder if they're from here though."
    St "Estos tipos parecen que podrían ayudar... aunque me pregunto si serán de aquí."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2323
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_a2d9e03a:

    # St "No... They look like passerbys. I need someone who looks like they're from here."
    St "No... Parecen transeúntes. Necesito a alguien que realmente parezca de aquí."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2331
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_eb7b0b39:

    # St "Wait, what about those guys over there. Rough looking, but not exactly the settler type."
    St "Espera, ¿qué pasa con esos de allí? Lucen rudos, pero no exactamente como colonos."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2332
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_6fe5c3cb:

    # St "I could be wrong, but I have to start somewhere."
    St "Podría equivocarme, pero tengo que empezar por algún lado."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2335
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_295edfa2:

    # "She approaches the men..."
    "Ella se acerca a los hombres..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2338
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_dd3d173c:

    # Man "That's a good blade... how did you obtain it?"
    Man "Esa es una buena hoja... ¿cómo la conseguiste?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2341
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_843eed50:

    # Merch "That's for me to know."
    Merch "Eso es cosa mía."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2342
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_4eb7d85d:

    # Merch "You want it or not?"
    Merch "¿Lo quieres o no?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2345
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_6ac31738:

    # Man "That depends... you think I can bite through leather armor with this?"
    Man "Depende... ¿crees que pueda atravesar una armadura de cuero con esto?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2348
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_da4b9c8c:

    # Merch "What would be the point of wearing leather armour, if swords did that?"
    Merch "¿Qué sentido tendría llevar armadura de cuero, si las espadas hicieran eso?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2349
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_88d86c88:

    # S "Excuse me... I have a few questions."
    S "Disculpen... Tengo unas preguntas."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2352
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_57bebac5:

    # Merch "Well, hello there. I bet I have some good answers for you."
    Merch "Vaya, hola. Apostaría a que tengo buenas respuestas para ti."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2355
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_978d26a0:

    # S "I need to speak to the man in charge of this place. I am looking for something, and I think he can help me."
    S "Necesito hablar con el responsable de este lugar. Estoy buscando algo, y creo que él puede ayudarme."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2358
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_baf2ef62:

    # Merch "The man in charge, huh?"
    Merch "¿El responsable, eh?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2361
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_6fe05f0f:

    # Merch "I doubt that fat manchild will be able to help you..."
    Merch "Dudo que ese gordo inmaduro pueda ayudarte..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2362
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_e5f91b26:

    # Merch "...but if you look at the tent behind you, he's probably in there, taking another one of his hour long naps."
    Merch "... pero si miras la tienda detrás de ti, probablemente esté allí, echándose otra de sus siestas de una hora."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2365
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_f97ea20a:

    # S "Oh, that one... I appreciate it."
    S "Ah, eso... Te lo agradezco."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2368
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_a6de78a4:

    # Man "Tell me, what does a young snack like you want to find in the desert?"
    Man "Dime, ¿qué quiere encontrar en el desierto un bocado joven como tú?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2369
translate spanish d19e_shani_bazaar_cadd671b:

    # Man "You look like you should rather be home, taking care of the kids I give you."
    Man "Pareces más del tipo que debería estar en casa, cuidando de los hijos que yo te daría."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2375
translate spanish d19e23_da7a22c7:

    # S "What did you call me?!"
    S "¿Cómo me llamaste?!"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2376
translate spanish d19e23_2c03804e:

    # Man "An snack. The weak ones in a group, who die first... and in cases like yours, the ones who I'd enjoy first after battle."
    Man "Un tentempié. Los débiles de un grupo, los que mueren primero... y en casos como el tuyo, los que disfruto primero tras la batalla."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2379
translate spanish d19e23_27aa3adc:

    # St "This... Does he really think this would work?"
    St "Esto... ¿De verdad cree que esto le va a funcionar?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2383
translate spanish d19e23_a72785fe:

    # St "It's best to evade this guy."
    St "Lo mejor es evitar a este tipo."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2386
translate spanish d19e23_87ae5c90:

    # S "I'm not looking for trouble. I need to get going."
    S "No busco problemas. Necesito seguir adelante."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2389
translate spanish d19e23_f48a5cfa:

    # Man "...and well mannered too, I'll be damned. A proper little lady, aren't you?"
    Man "...y bien educada también, maldita sea. Toda una señorita, ¿verdad?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2392
translate spanish d19e23_c30b2394:

    # Man "If I wouldn't care about my reputation in this place, I'd drag you to my tent and show you what happens to naive incautious girls like you."
    Man "Si no me importara mi reputación aquí, te arrastraría a mi tienda y te mostraría lo que les pasa a chicas ingenuas e imprudentes como tú."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2393
translate spanish d19e23_52087c13:

    # Man "Don't let the chief's hands ruin your innocence..."
    Man "No dejes que las manos del jefe arruinen tu inocencia..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2397
translate spanish d19e23_818c31ff:

    # "He sneers at [S] as she turns around, a crass laugh ringing in her ears..."
    "Se burla de [S] mientras ella se da la vuelta, una risa vulgar resonando en sus oídos..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2400
translate spanish d19e23_338fefc8:

    # St "Just another one of those. Best to ignore him and move forward."
    St "Solo otro como tantos. Mejor ignorarlo y seguir adelante."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2407
translate spanish d19e23_921e9243:

    # S "Tell me, is this how you usually talk to Desert Stalkers?"
    S "Dime, ¿así es como sueles hablarle a los Acechadores del Desierto?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2410
translate spanish d19e23_60cdbc69:

    # St "I bet he didn't expect that."
    St "Apuesto a que no se esperaba eso."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2411
translate spanish d19e23_febffd67:

    # Man "{i}*laughs*{/i} No, I don't."
    Man "{i}*risas*{/i} No, no lo hago."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2412
translate spanish d19e23_013cbe5a:

    # Man "I usually creep up on them from behind, and stab them in the back for their gold. Why do you ask?"
    Man "Normalmente me acerco por detrás, y los apuñalo en la espalda por su oro. ¿Por qué lo preguntas?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2415
translate spanish d19e23_971a98df:

    # S "..."
    S "..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2416
translate spanish d19e23_1f20e5ae:

    # Man "Was I too direct for you?"
    Man "¿Fui demasiado directo para ti?"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2419
translate spanish d19e23_014b05dd:

    # Man "Don't worry. In your case, I can make an exception..."
    Man "No te preocupes. En tu caso, puedo hacer una excepción..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2423
translate spanish d19e23_69ae1807:

    # St "Ouch...! Did he just...?!"
    St "¡Ay...! ¡¿Acaba de...?!"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2424
translate spanish d19e23_f5f0e0c8:

    # Man "...this pretty ass should serve other purposes."
    Man "... este lindo culo debería servir para otros fines."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2425
translate spanish d19e23_1fd3de95:

    # Man "In fact, why don't you come with me. I can get you all the information you need, in exchange for a favour..."
    Man "De hecho, ¿por qué no vienes conmigo? Puedo darte toda la información que necesites, a cambio de un favor..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2430
translate spanish d19e23_bcef3423:

    # S "Bastard..."
    S "Bastardo..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2433
translate spanish d19e23_51713537:

    # Man "{i}*laughs*{/i} I hear that a lot."
    Man "{i}*risas*{/i} Eso lo oigo muy a menudo."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2434
translate spanish d19e23_c84467f5:

    # Man "Go on, beg the chief for some of that information, \"Stalker\"..."
    Man "Anda, suplica al jefe por un poco de esa información, \"Acechadora\"..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2438
translate spanish d19e23_a3c68a48:

    # S "...!"
    S "¡...!"

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2439
translate spanish d19e23_7a52c7b8:

    # Man "Here, another one to remember me by..."
    Man "toma, otro para que me recuerdes..."

# game/scripts/day19.rpy:2442
translate spanish d19e23_71fcad91:

